cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the implementation of a distribution market operator (DMO) for electricity markets, which involves the use of optimization and game theory techniques to clear and settle the market. This falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY), as well as game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG) since the DMO uses machine learning algorithms to predict demand and supply. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of locational marginal pricing (LMP) to calculate payments, which is a common technique used in computational engineering (cs.CE) and software engineering (cs.SE) for optimization problems.
